In the following code cell, we add one more step to the data pipelines from the previous two parts. The new step uses slice_head(n = 1), which is designed to give the first row of the output. Run each and analyze the result. You will notice the results are different. Why?


# pipeline from part b + slice_head()
df_2 |&gt;
  group_by(shift, member) |&gt;
  summarize(mean_hours = mean(hours)) |&gt;
  slice_head(n = 1)

# pipeline from part c + slice_head()
df_2 |&gt;
  group_by(shift, member) |&gt;
  summarize(mean_hours = mean(hours), .groups = "drop") |&gt;
  slice_head(n = 1)


